    ],
    "summary": "On 21 April 2023 at 0938 hours, the TO Discoverer Inspiration drillship experienced an intense frontal passage with 67 knot winds during well abandonment operations. The drillship began drifting off location, requiring activation of the Emergency Disconnect System (EDS). This resulted in discharge of 513 barrels of calcium bromide into Gulf of Mexico waters. Two thrusters (#4 and #6) were operating at reduced power during the event for unknown reasons. No injuries, muster, or equipment damage occurred. The EDS performed as intended.",
    "recommendations": [
      "No recommendations made by BSEE Lafayette District"
    ],
